From 4d8688c48cec22dec77a0813ac94834b42557888 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dan on Selwyn <dan@awto.au>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 17:04:42 +1000
Subject: [PATCH 12/20] firmware+scripts: fault injection verbs and test script
 for #14/#16
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

selftest GCP class gains four new verbs:
  0x00  get_canary_status  — safe probe: returns canary word, stack used/total
  0x11  trigger_panic      — deliberate panic!() to test panic handler
  0x12  trigger_stack_overflow — unbounded recursion; canary fires on next IRQ
  0x13  corrupt_canary     — overwrites _sheap; returns OK, panic ~1ms later

canary module gains read_raw() and corrupt() for fault injection support.

scripts/test-fault-detection.py: CLI runner that verifies canary is intact
(safe, always runnable) and optionally drives all three destructive fault
paths with pass/fail reporting. --destructive requires reset between tests.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 firmware/moondancer/src/canary.rs       |  13 ++
 firmware/moondancer/src/gcp/selftest.rs | 129 ++++++++++++++++--
 scripts/test-fault-detection.py         | 169 ++++++++++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 301 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)
